The paper deals with the complexity of counting cliques in random hypergraphs, which is a problem in computational complexity (cs.CC). The problem is related to graph theory (cs.DM) and algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also discusses phase transitions and information-computation gaps, which are topics in theoretical computer science (cs.GT) and information theory (cs.IT).
